<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-19T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2014</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-19T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 19,
                                            1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your June 13, 5 p.m. Department believes reasonable quantity of
                                material for Moscow Supply Committee should be released and
                                forwarded as trial shipment. When shipment is made full information
                                should be furnished Department to communicate to consular
                                representatives in Siberia and European Russia, so that they can
                                follow shipments to destination. Department has just approved
                                shipment from this country to Moscow Supply Committee 50,000 pairs
                                shoes as trial shipment to be delivered to representative of
                                committee at Omsk.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>